<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Ragon der Magier on 04-21-2002 09:57 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">You could also make either the [i]"Age..."[/i] or the [i]"Sword..."[/i] into a [i]"... of Deceit"[/i] or [i]"... of Treason"[/i], words descending from the same family of meanings.
That압 just for staying within some given "frame".

Actually i앐 not particularly enthusiastic about the weapon/artifacts naming as it e.g. already shows in one of the new "sixpack" - to awfully Diablo-like! Nay!   :down:   :rolleyes:
Those lenghty composited names are just too long and thereby turn out more ridiculous than anything.
You should rather put such info as "enchanted" or what kind of enchantment an item features (magical or through craftmanship) or the status of it in terms of durability/how worn out it is, into some few explaining lines within its attributes window!
If you could include some brief history of the item at least for unique weapons/equipment and maybe reduced to only what common knowledge can tell (though youre invited to make it so that it will be enhanced while the player압 character advances through the story occasionally!   >:)), it surely would be welcomed.
That all available after proper identification only, of course!   >:)   ;)

As far as it is now (and has been already in [i]Diablo[/i]) it압 just quite bothering with all that squeezing them into those few naming categories multiplied then just with another uniform set of categories, giving it an all too "mechanical feel" and at the same time taking away from atmosphere and suspension of disbelief in    :div:압 otherwise so positively complex and detailed world.
Just wouldn앖 be appropriate this current way!
You also should rather include the names of a previous (in)famous possessor of the weapon/item, the one of its maker or the place of its making for its label.
Maybe a location could be famous for its magically enhanced or well crafted weapons, or a certain sorceror/race. The same for more powerful magical artifacts. And in the same sense a certain ancient and legendary weapon smith might "take over responsibility" for some of your "arsenal"!  ;)  :D
Just let your fantasy play! And do not overdo with well crafted+enchanted+divine+blessed thingys etc., pleaaase! (would make the names just unbearably long in your current diction anyway!   ;)   >:))
Oh, the material is of course another means of differentiation - but that also has been recognized by the makers of [i]Diablo[/i] before.
What would they be? Bronze, Iron, Steel, better avoid silver as it makes not much sense besides for ceremonial purposes or as far as it would have "special effects" on dedicated monster categories, and then of course "the" fantasy weapon material - [i]mithr巖[/i]! Maybe s.o. else can think of more.
But that [i]"Master Assassin압 Broad Axe of Lightning Flashes"[/i] is just too plain awful and leaves a bad taste (yeah, know that it isn앖 for yourself to taste from it, but for your enemy!   ;)   :D   :p)!

Sorry, but that압 the way it immediately jumps into my mind!   ;)   :(

Ragon, the Critic

